title: Honor 8 Pro with dual cameras reportedly launching at MWC
text:
Honor 8 Pro with dual cameras reportedly launching at MWC Honor 8 Pro with dual cameras reportedly launching at MWC By - February 20, 2017 “The Honor 8 Pro will be a flagship offering with two 12MP cameras at the back” 
Honor is all set to launch the Honor V9 and Honor 8 Youth Edition smartphones in its home market of China on February 21st. The Honor V9 will be a flagship offering with two rear cameras, and initially will be exclusive to China Mobile’s subscribers. Now a new report suggests that after an unveiling in China, Honor will launch the Honor V9 globally at its MWC event on February 27th in Barcelona. 
As per the reports, the Honor 8 Pro or Honor V9 will flaunt two 12-megapixel cameras at the back and an 8-megapixel shooter in the front. The phone will sport a 5.7-inch quad-HD display, and will boot Android Nougat out of the box. It will come with a 2.4GHz octa-core Kirin SoC, 6GB of RAM, 128GB of storage, a fingerprint sensor, an all-metal design and a 3,900mAh battery with fast charging support. We will have its pricing and availability details at MWC later this month.
